    <StatementCodes>
      <StatementCode>CCSS.Math.Content.8.EE.A.1</StatementCode>
    </StatementCodes>
    <Statements>
      <Statement>Know and apply the properties of integer exponents to generate equivalent numerical expressions. For example, 3&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;times;&amp;nbsp;3&lt;sup&gt;&amp;ndash;5&lt;/sup&gt; = 3&lt;sup&gt;&amp;ndash;3&lt;/sup&gt; = 1/3&lt;sup&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt; = 1/27.</Statement>
    </Statements>
